# Ecosystem Compute/Infra Master Plan & Absorption Deletion-Justification Package

**Date:** 2026-06-23  
**Author:** Forge (compute/infra ecosystem owner)  
**Status:** LIVE - guiding all compute/infra absorption + DAG execution  

---

## EXECUTIVE DECISION

**Decision:** `DELETE_AFTER_PATCHES` for absorption targets; `PRESERVE_AND_ENHANCE` for core compute repos.

**Confidence:** HIGH

**Rationale:**
The compute/infra ecosystem has four **active, maintained, production-quality core repos** (phenotype-infra, nanovms, PhenoCompose, BytePort) that implement a full 3-tier microVM isolation stack with Go orchestration + Rust FFI + web frontend. These are **not deprecated** — they need continued investment and stabilization. Separately, there are 8+ **absorption targets** (kodevibego, agentapi, kodevibe, kvirtualstage, kdesktopvirt, pheno-sdk, argisexec, thegent-workspace) that must have their meaningful content migrated into the core repos or the registry, after which they can be deleted. This plan produces per-repo deletion-justification matrices, the absorption DAG, and the compute/infra enhancement roadmap.

